->if an interface contain only one abstract method , such type of interfaces are called functional interfaces and the method is called functional method or single abstract method(SAM).
EX:::
->Runnable=it contains only run() method
->Comparable=it comtains only compareTo() method
->ActionListener=it contains only actionPerformed() method
->Callable=it contains only call() method
note::::::inside functional interface in addition to single abstract method(SAM)
we write any number of default and static methods...
:::::::::::::::::::::::::;example one:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
interface Test6{
public abstract void display(int a,int b);
//default and static methods are java 8 features
default void m1(){
System.out.println("hello");
}
public static void m2(){
System.out.println("hi");
}
public static void main(String args[]){
m2();
}
}


